               <p>AFTER the case was gone through on the part of the prosecution, it appeared that the sum paid to the prisoner by Mr. Levi, was paid in bank notes, and</p>

               <p>MR. WALFORD. After commenting to the Jury with a considerable degree of vivacity and warmth of expression on the part of the prisoner, insisted on the acquittal of his client, because bank notes were not money, and the indictment stated that the consideration was paid in money.</p>

               <p>THE COURT. Co-incided with the learned Counsel's objection, and the Jury found the prisoner</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t18160403-102-verdict518" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18160403-102-verdict518" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160403-102-verdict518" type="verdictSubcategory" value="fault"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>

               <p>London Jury, before Mr. Recorder.</p>
